handNote.desc:
The handwriting displays old paleographic features:
ሎ has the loop marking the 7th order attached directly to the body of the letter, without the linking line;
the upper part of the letters ቆ, ቶ, የ, ደ, ጸ has an angular shape;
መ and ዐ have angular loops;
ግዚ in the word እግዚአብሔር፡ is usually written with ligature;
the old spelling እግዜኣብሔር፡ is rarely found.
